DOC.HEAD: NEW YORK: not materialize.
DOC.TEXT: The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell 42.02 to 2,697.53, for its biggest single-day loss since it dropped 47.34 points on Nov. 6. Declining issues outnumbered advances by more than 7 to 2 on the New York Stock Exchange, with 350 up, 1,279 down and 359 unchanged.. Big Board volume came to an estimated 187 million shares, against 240.39 million in the previous session. The NYSE's composite index dropped 3.28 to 190.17.
